is a lot bigger.

30:20.621 --> 30:22.155
Oh, wow, really?
How many pieces?

30:22.188 --> 30:23.223
Twenty‐nine.

30:23.256 --> 30:24.658
Whoa!

30:24.691 --> 30:26.126
Twenty‐nine‐piece kit.

30:26.159 --> 30:28.862
Wow, what are you doing here?
You should be auditioning us.

30:28.895 --> 30:31.397
Pshhh! Yeah, right.
Right?

30:31.431 --> 30:34.935
Ha ha. I saw you guys
open for Jethro Tull

30:34.968 --> 30:36.570
at Cobo Hall last year.

30:36.603 --> 30:38.471
You guys blew them away.

30:38.505 --> 30:39.973
Well, you must've been
there Friday night,

30:40.006 --> 30:41.575
'cause Saturday night
we got booed off the stage.

30:41.608 --> 30:43.510
We didn't get booed
off the stage.

30:44.210 --> 30:45.478
(LAUGHS)

30:45.512 --> 30:47.514
So what do you say?
You wanna jam or what?

30:48.515 --> 30:49.850
Yeah!
Cool.

30:49.883 --> 30:52.052
Let's rock it, man.

30:52.085 --> 30:53.086
Cool.

30:53.720 --> 30:55.689
You call the tune.

30:55.722 --> 30:57.758
Uh... How about
a little Cream?

30:57.791 --> 30:59.593
Yeah, let's do <i>Crossroads.</i>

30:59.626 --> 31:02.929
What do you, uh, what about
<i>Sunshine Of Your Love?</i>

31:02.963 --> 31:04.931
I hate that song.
Let's do <i>Crossroads.</i>

31:04.965 --> 31:06.399
We do it live.

31:07.968 --> 31:09.002
No problem.

31:09.035 --> 31:11.004
All right.
Count it off, my man.

31:14.641 --> 31:15.642
NICK: All right.

31:16.577 --> 31:17.578
Yeah.

31:33.026 --> 31:35.495
That's good, but let's
try it a little bit tighter.

31:35.529 --> 31:36.563
Tighter?

31:36.597 --> 31:37.931
Yeah.
All right. Let's do it.

31:37.964 --> 31:39.566
Count it off.
Right.

31:51.712 --> 31:54.147
Hold it.
Hold it.

31:54.180 --> 31:58.084
Hold on. Let's try it
just a little bit
quicker pace.

31:59.620 --> 32:00.887
Oh, quicker pace.

32:00.921 --> 32:03.123
Yeah.
Okay. Cool.

32:07.728 --> 32:09.495
Sorry 'bout that.
Ready?

32:09.530 --> 32:10.597
All right,
here we go.

32:10.631 --> 32:11.998
Count it off.

32:32.819 --> 32:35.556
<i>♪♪ I went down to</i>
<i>the crossroads</i>

32:35.589 --> 32:37.591
<i>♪♪ Got down on my knees</i>

32:40.493 --> 32:45.098
<i>♪♪ Got to the crossroads,</i>
<i>dropped down on my knees</i>

32:46.266 --> 32:50.637
♪♪ Asked the lord for mercy...

32:56.910 --> 32:59.179
Good. All right.
Great job, man.

33:00.146 --> 33:01.347
Cool. Thanks a lot.

33:02.415 --> 33:04.450
What do you mean?
That's it?

33:04.484 --> 33:05.519
Well, that's it?

33:05.552 --> 33:07.754
Yeah. Thanks a lot.

33:07.788 --> 33:09.222
I... I, uh...

33:09.255 --> 33:11.725
Hey, uh, good luck with
that 29‐piecer, man.

33:11.758 --> 33:14.528
Maybe someday, you'll knock
it up to an even 30.

33:16.663 --> 33:17.664
Thanks.

33:32.245 --> 33:34.314
So, what are you
gonna do now?

33:36.082 --> 33:38.018
Join the army,
I guess.

33:39.786 --> 33:42.455
No. I mean...
Right now.

33:42.488 --> 33:44.791
Do you want to go
to the record store
or anything?

33:44.825 --> 33:46.392
I suck, Lindsay.

33:46.426 --> 33:47.561
No, you don't.

33:50.531 --> 33:52.398
You were in there
with me, right?

33:53.133 --> 33:55.101
You... You heard me playing?

33:56.069 --> 33:57.538
I was a joke.

33:58.905 --> 34:03.443
You know, Nick, those guys
are 5 years older than you.

34:03.476 --> 34:06.246
And in 5 years,
you're gonna be
way better than they are.

34:08.582 --> 34:09.716
No, I'm not.

34:13.887 --> 34:15.889
Sometimes I go down
in my basement,

34:15.922 --> 34:18.024
and I put on a live album,

34:18.058 --> 34:21.361
I can...
See myself on the stage.

34:21.394 --> 34:23.429
Do you understand
what I mean? I can see it.

34:23.463 --> 34:24.798
And I'm playing
a 10‐minute solo,

34:24.831 --> 34:27.968
and I'm on one of those
hydraulic risers, you know,

34:28.001 --> 34:30.070
that make the drum kit
go way up high.

34:30.103 --> 34:32.506
I'm Peter Criss or something.

34:35.375 --> 34:36.577
Oh, man...

34:41.114 --> 34:43.283
I'm not gonna be that guy.

34:43.316 --> 34:45.085
I'm never gonna be
that guy.

34:47.253 --> 34:49.089
I'll be lucky if I
get to be the guy

34:49.122 --> 34:51.091
who pushes the button
and makes the riser go up,

34:51.124 --> 34:53.193
but I'm not even gonna be
that guy.

34:53.994 --> 34:55.161
I'm not even gonna be
that guy

34:55.195 --> 34:58.398
'cause I can't
even keep a C+ average, man.

34:58.431 --> 35:02.536
Oh, Nick, I could...
I can help you
get your grades up.

35:03.469 --> 35:05.371
He's gonna make me
join the army.

35:06.406 --> 35:09.242
Oh, man, I'm gonna have
to join the army.

35:09.275 --> 35:11.411
I'm gonna be surrounded
by a group of psychopaths

35:11.444 --> 35:14.715
like my brothers
and like my dad.

35:14.748 --> 35:17.784
Nick, come on.

35:18.552 --> 35:20.486
That's not gonna
happen to you.

35:21.688 --> 35:22.956
I won't let it.

35:22.989 --> 35:24.390
Oh, my God.

35:26.492 --> 35:27.794
I'm done, man.

35:29.630 --> 35:30.631
I'm done.

36:17.477 --> 36:21.682
<i>♪♪ In a white room</i>
<i>with black curtains</i>

36:21.715 --> 36:24.585
<i>♪♪ Near the station</i>

36:26.186 --> 36:30.190
<i>♪♪ Black roof country</i>
<i>No gold pavements</i>

36:30.223 --> 36:33.393
<i>♪♪ Tired stylings</i>

36:34.928 --> 36:36.730
<i>♪♪ Silver horses</i>

36:36.763 --> 36:42.335
<i>♪♪ Run down moonbeams</i>
<i>in your dark eyes</i>

36:44.070 --> 36:48.041
<i>♪♪ Dark light smile</i>
<i>on you leaving</i>

36:48.074 --> 36:50.443
<i>♪♪ My contentment ♪♪</i>

36:54.480 --> 36:56.249
NEAL: What is wrong
with them?

36:56.282 --> 36:58.218
Why do they think
that hitting people

36:58.251 --> 36:59.753
with towels is so funny?

37:00.687 --> 37:02.556
If it wasn't us...

37:02.589 --> 37:05.358
Ha ha ha...
It would be kinda funny.

37:06.226 --> 37:07.728
BOY: Afternoon,
gentlemen.

37:10.096 --> 37:12.498
Hey, have you lost weight?

37:13.967 --> 37:15.368
Shut up!

37:17.237 --> 37:18.939
Get out of my way.

37:18.972 --> 37:20.874
I'm gonna take
a shower.

37:24.545 --> 37:27.447
Look who finally decided
to take a shower.

37:28.148 --> 37:30.116
Nice pecs, Weir.

37:30.150 --> 37:32.586
You look like
a flat‐chested girl.

37:32.619 --> 37:34.521
Ha ha!
Flat‐chested girl.

37:35.922 --> 37:38.024
Well, I'm proud
of my body.

37:38.058 --> 37:40.761
(MOCKINGLY)
oh, he's proud of his body.

37:40.794 --> 37:42.929
Oh, he should be proud.
Look at this.

37:42.963 --> 37:44.030
Get out of my way.

37:44.064 --> 37:46.099
Maybe you should show it
to everybody then, huh, Weir?

37:46.132 --> 37:48.368
What are you doing?

37:48.401 --> 37:51.505
Come on, guys.
Guys, don't...

37:51.538 --> 37:53.439
I wouldn't want you
to miss class.

37:56.843 --> 37:57.878
Oh, come on!

37:57.911 --> 37:59.946
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

37:59.980 --> 38:02.415
Let me in!
Mr. Fredricks!

38:02.448 --> 38:04.785
So, uh, how long
have you been teaching?

38:04.818 --> 38:05.852
2 months.

38:05.886 --> 38:07.654
2 months?
Do you like it?

38:07.688 --> 38:09.422
I love it.
I love it, too.

38:09.890 --> 38:11.224
Mr. Fredricks!

38:11.257 --> 38:13.059
Oh, I'm sorry, Weir.

38:14.194 --> 38:15.696
I forgot to take that!

38:18.131 --> 38:19.165
God!

38:19.199 --> 38:20.834
(BULLIES LAUGH)

38:28.441 --> 38:29.976
Got some shorts
in my locker.

38:35.281 --> 38:37.651
(BELL RINGS)

38:37.684 --> 38:39.553
(GASPS)

38:46.059 --> 38:47.060
Why...

38:51.331 --> 38:52.799
Sam, Alan's gone.

38:52.833 --> 38:55.401
All clear,
you can come back now.

38:58.739 --> 39:00.340
Hey, Lindsay.

39:00.807 --> 39:02.676
Hi.
Hey.

39:02.709 --> 39:04.911
Can I talk to you
for a second?

39:05.378 --> 39:06.980
Yeah. Sure.

39:07.013 --> 39:08.448
Come on.

39:12.919 --> 39:14.087
Streaker!

39:14.120 --> 39:15.622
Go, Sam! Go!

39:36.510 --> 39:37.544
Where you from?

39:37.578 --> 39:38.612
I'm from right here.

39:38.645 --> 39:40.213
I actually live
down the street.

39:40.246 --> 39:41.347
You're from
right here?

39:41.381 --> 39:42.649
Yeah.
Oh, my...

39:44.985 --> 39:47.387
Yeah, right.
You know...

39:48.054 --> 39:49.055
Oh, Jesus.

39:52.926 --> 39:56.062
Well, what the hell
are you looking at?

39:57.263 --> 40:00.000
Weir...
The shower's that way.

40:04.237 --> 40:05.506
I just wanted you to know

40:05.539 --> 40:07.674
I can't stop thinking
about that kiss.

40:08.141 --> 40:09.676
Oh, good.

40:12.045 --> 40:13.914
It really meant a lot to me.

40:14.881 --> 40:16.082
I'm glad.

40:18.652 --> 40:20.587
Let's go out to the patio.

40:20.987 --> 40:21.955
Patio?

40:21.988 --> 40:23.624
I thought you were fighting
with those guys.

40:23.657 --> 40:25.659
Yeah, we were,
but not anymore.

40:25.692 --> 40:28.061
We fight like that
all the time.
It doesn't mean anything.

40:28.094 --> 40:29.262
Oh...

40:29.295 --> 40:30.831
They heard what happened
at the audition.

40:30.864 --> 40:32.599
They came over last night,
we're cool.

40:33.867 --> 40:35.802
KIM: You know, you guys,
I'm serious.

40:35.836 --> 40:37.137
I think my mom, like,
wants to come

40:37.170 --> 40:38.639
see the band
play or something.

40:38.672 --> 40:40.173
When she gets
out of rehab?

40:40.206 --> 40:41.842
Oh, ho ho.
Shut up.

40:42.543 --> 40:45.045
Yah!
Yay!

40:45.078 --> 40:46.613
Ringo Starr.

40:46.647 --> 40:48.782
You finally got
your wish, Nick.

40:48.815 --> 40:51.084
You're as good a drummer
as John Bonham.

40:51.117 --> 40:52.218
Of course he's dead.

40:52.252 --> 40:53.887
(LAUGHTER)

40:53.920 --> 40:56.056
You should've seen the looks
on those guys' faces, man.

40:56.089 --> 40:58.892
I think I ruined their love
of music forever.

41:01.528 --> 41:02.963
Hey, is Dimension
gonna charge you

41:02.996 --> 41:05.031
for the pee stain you
left on the drum seat?

41:05.065 --> 41:06.299
Shut up.

41:06.332 --> 41:08.501
Look, Dimension sucks, man.

41:08.535 --> 41:10.571
You're too good for them.
I saw them open for Tull,

41:10.604 --> 41:12.172
they got booed off the stage.

41:13.173 --> 41:14.641
Thanks a lot, man.

41:16.643 --> 41:20.113
(MOUTHING)
hey Lindsay, we have to talk.

41:20.146 --> 41:21.782
DANIEL: So are we gonna
rehearse at your place today,

41:21.815 --> 41:22.849
or is the old man
gonna pop a vein?

41:22.883 --> 41:24.785
(MOUTHING)
you are such a slut.

41:24.818 --> 41:26.486
NICK: No. It's cool.
We just gotta be out by 5:00.

41:26.520 --> 41:28.454
DANIEL: Hey, let's play some
real songs for once.

41:28.488 --> 41:30.557
I wrote out some Iggy Pop
and Ramones songs.

41:30.591 --> 41:31.892
The Ramones?

41:31.925 --> 41:34.460
The Ramones only play,
like, 3 chords.

41:34.494 --> 41:36.262
All right, so I'll
learn another one.

41:36.296 --> 41:38.431
I gotta pee.

41:38.464 --> 41:41.467
I heard that you jumped him.
What?

41:41.501 --> 41:42.603
You don't have to
act innocent, Lindsay,

41:42.636 --> 41:44.070
I know you're a slut.

41:45.706 --> 41:47.808
NEAL: I'm pretty sure
Cindy didn't see you.

41:47.841 --> 41:51.444
And if she did, it was just
with her peripheral vision.

41:51.477 --> 41:53.747
Hey, it wouldn't be bad
if people saw my back.

41:53.780 --> 41:56.182
But my front's
a whole other story, you know?

41:57.918 --> 42:00.486
Maybe I could transfer
to another school.

42:00.521 --> 42:02.656
Well, well, well.

42:04.490 --> 42:07.260
Hey, Weir, that was fun
in gym class today, huh?

42:08.028 --> 42:09.429
Leave me alone.

42:09.462 --> 42:10.797
I heard they're bringing
in the psychiatrist

42:10.831 --> 42:12.999
for all the kids who
had to see you naked.

42:13.033 --> 42:14.535
Shut up, Alan.

42:14.568 --> 42:16.737
Whoo!
Whoo!

42:16.770 --> 42:18.539
Hey, Sam, I heard
you streaked!

42:18.572 --> 42:20.273
Way to go!

42:20.306 --> 42:23.009
(CHEERING)

42:23.043 --> 42:24.545
Shut up!

42:26.112 --> 42:28.214
All right, Sam.

42:29.950 --> 42:32.553
You guys are losers,
and you always will be.

42:34.120 --> 42:36.923
How come you're the one
riding home with no friends?

42:39.125 --> 42:41.327
You're like a god.

42:41.361 --> 42:42.796
People are gonna
worship you.

42:45.431 --> 42:47.267
(PLAYING ALONG
WITH RECORDING)

43:12.859 --> 43:15.696
I play so much better
when you're around.

43:17.363 --> 43:20.701
Hey, I want to play it again.
Put more dry ice
in the bucket.

43:21.835 --> 43:22.836
Sure.

43:28.141 --> 43:29.142
Thanks.
